---
const { variant } = Astro.props;
---

<div class="container">
  <div class="container__content--left">
    <!-- Some content here -->
    <slot name="left">
      <aside>
        {
          variant === "first" && (
            <blockquote>
              This is the left sticky content. It will stay at the top of the
              viewport as you scroll through the center content. And on small
              screens this will stack on top. Depending on the content, you may
              want this to stick to the top of the page as you scroll.
              <img src="https://media0.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExcTd1dHF2Y2NhdjJ4M2h5YjRkcXAydnNpaWZ4YWIzNzg5emM2dWpjaiZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/cFiBfS6f4Ea4fScrFn/giphy.gif" />
            </blockquote>
          )
        }

        {
          variant === "next" && (
            <blockquote>
              And if this pattern is encapsulated in a component, we can render
              a stack of these <code>StickySide</code> components and have
              written content scroll in and out of the viewport
              <img src="https://media4.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExZjZ6Zm1vZ3hvOGR5ODdsNWtrazRiZWtwdm5jZHJybjFrNGVwaHE2ZSZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/XQdfOzuQOCj4qb2jW6/giphy.gif" />
            </blockquote>
          )
        }
      </aside>
    </slot>
  </div>
  <div class="container__content--center">
    <!-- Long list of content to scroll through like images -->
    <slot />
  </div>
  <div class="container__content--right">
    <!-- Some content here -->
    <slot name="right">
      <aside>
        {
          variant === "first" && (
            <blockquote>
              This is the right sticky content. It will stay at the bottom of
              the viewport as you scroll through the center content.And on small
              screens this will stack on the bottom. Same thing here - depending
              on the content you have, you may want this to stick to the bottom
              of the page.
              <img src="https://media2.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExbDdyOTY5azdndzAxaDBya3d6YnVhcGk5dzVta3hpZWV2NWRpd3o4MSZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/zywaBv69BUzFAJpFli/giphy.gif" />
            </blockquote>
          )
        }
        {
          variant === "last" && (
            <blockquote>
              Pretty neat!
              <img src="https://media4.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExYTE2eWNiN3R4cHliajM0cDVseHMwZ3M1eGExOG14N3lybXFlNnJzcyZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/ardUtH5FlenO8/giphy.gif" />
            </blockquote>
          )
        }
      </aside>
    </slot>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  /* css */
  .container {
    /* Blog uses 3 column layout - make sure container spans all 3 columns */
    grid-column: 1 / span 3;
    position: relative;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 64ch 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .container__content--left {
    position: sticky;
    top: 1rem;
    align-self: start;
    /* padding-block-start: 1rem; */
    justify-self: end;
  }

  .container__content--center {
    /* No styles needed here. 
  Content will simply stack on top of each other so you can scroll through it. */
    /* padding-inline: 16rem !important; */
  }

  .container__content--right {
    position: sticky;
    bottom: 1rem;
    align-self: end;
    padding-block-end: 1rem;
  }

  .container__content--left > *,
  .container__content--right > * {
    max-inline-size: 32ch;
  }

  /* small screens */
  @media screen and (width < 1280px) {
    .container {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .container__content--center {
      padding-inline: 1rem !important;
    }

    .container__content--left,
    .container__content--right {
      position: static;
      max-inline-size: 64ch;
      margin: 0 auto;
      margin-block-end: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
